      "content": "thanks. the ghost thing is a bit dramatic lol but i get what u mean. i looked at the state_variable issue and it seems like it only triggers when the timeout happens first. so it's like a chain reaction. \n\nbeyond just the code bug, why do u think this is only happening during peak traffic? like, why would a simple NameError and a timeout only show up when the load is high? it feels almost random.",
